According to the United Nations Office for the Co-ordination of Humanitarian Affairs, another 28 000 have also fled into Uganda. There is a long history of tensions between the Lendu and Hema groups, whose ongoing battles since 1999 already have killed thousands and led the UN to deploy a peacekeeping force in the area. Much of it is rooted in economic tensions over land, as the Lendu historically have been farmers while the Hema raised animals and moved throughout the year to good grazing places. --AP--